# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
# RIDER MOTORPARTS — Environment Variables
# Copy this to .env and fill in your values
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════

# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from: https://supabase.com → Your Project → Settings → API
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES:
#
# For VERCEL:
# 1. Go to Project Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Add SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 3. In js/config.js, the keys are already set up
#    to read from window.ENV_* variables
#
# For NETLIFY:
# 1. Go to Site Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Add SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY
# 3. The netlify/functions/book-appointment.js uses
#    process.env.SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY
#
# For LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Fill in your actual values
# 3. Replace the placeholder strings in js/config.js directly
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
